    "# Rename columns and make them type string for later operations\n",
    "road_links.rename(columns={'u': 'from', 'v': 'to'}, inplace=True)\n",
    "road_nodes['osmid'] = road_nodes['osmid'].astype(str)\n",
    "road_nodes = road_nodes.set_index('osmid')[['geometry']]\n",
    "road_links[['from', 'to']] = road_links[['from', 'to']].astype(str)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We can drastically reduce the disc space needed for this table by\n",
    "# reducing the complexity of LineString geometries.\n",
    "# For our purpose it is enough to have the start and end point of a link.\n",
    "# Let's write a function\n",
    "def simplify_link(g):\n",
    "    l = list(g.coords)\n",
    "    return geometry.LineString([l[0], l[-1]])\n",
    "# Apply the function to all our links\n",
    "road_links['geometry'] = road_links['geometry'].apply(simplify_link)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a cleaner object and run cleaning functions on it\n",
    "oc = OsmnxCleaner(\n",
    "    road_links, \n",
    "    road_nodes, \n",
    "    a='from', \n",
    "    b='to'\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "oc.add_reversed_links(\n",
    "    direction_column='oneway', \n",
    "    reverse_value=False # the boolean has been stored as a string    \n",
    ")\n",
    "#oc.clean_geometries() # Doesn't work, but let's hope we don't need it\n",
    "oc.fix_nodeset_consistency()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "## Public Transport\n",
    "\n",
    "For PT, we need to convert GTFS feeds into links and nodes GeoDataFrames"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load the GTFS feed\n",
    "full_feed = importer.GtfsImporter(path=input_folder + r'/IDFM_gtfs.zip', dist_units='m') \n",
    "# downloaded from https://data.iledefrance-mobilites.fr/explore/dataset/offre-horaires-tc-gtfs-idf/table/"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Restrict the feed to a given date in order to analyse a\n",
    "# typical work day and not the whole week\n",
    "feed_r = full_feed.restrict(\n",
    "    dates=['20200204'] # the dates must be within the feed start and end dates\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We can also restrict it to hours\n",
    "time_range = ['08:00:00', '09:00:00'] \n",
    "feed_t = feed_r.restrict(time_range=time_range)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# And we can restrict it spacially if we write a suitable function\n",
    "def spatial_restrict(feed, polygon, how='inner'):\n",
    "    f = feed.copy()\n",
    "    stops = f.stops.copy()\n",
    "    stops['geometry'] = stops.apply(\n",
    "        lambda r: geometry.Point([r['stop_lon'], r['stop_lat']]),\n",
    "        axis=1\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    stops['included'] = stops['geometry'].apply(lambda g: polygon.contains(g))\n",
    "    f.stops = f.stops.loc[stops['included'] == True]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # relations\n",
    "    f.stop_times = f.stop_times.loc[f.stop_times['stop_id'].isin(f.stops['stop_id'])]\n",
    "    f.transfers = f.transfers.loc[f.transfers['from_stop_id'].isin(f.stops['stop_id'])]\n",
    "    f.transfers = f.transfers.loc[f.transfers['to_stop_id'].isin(f.stops['stop_id'])]\n",
    "    relevant_trips = (f.stop_times['trip_id'])\n",
    "    f = f.restrict(trip_ids=relevant_trips)\n",
    "    if how == 'inner':\n",
    "        return f\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return feed.restrict(trip_ids=relevant_trips)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Give the hourly restricted feed to the spatial restriction\n",
    "feed_s = spatial_restrict(feed_t, polygon=hull, how='inner')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "# Rename the route types\n",
    "mapping = {0:'tram', 1:'subway', 2:'rail', 3:'bus',\n",

    "\n",
    "feed_frequencies.links['route_type'] = feed_frequencies.links['route_type'].apply(\n",
    "    lambda t: mapping.get(t, t)\n",
    ")"
   ]
